  "abstract": "Experiments were conducted in greenhouse with groundnut (Arachis hypogaea) variety JL 24 (highly susceptible to PBNV, TSV and IPCV) to determine the effect of plant growth stage to the infection with PBNV, TSC and IPCV. Groundnut plants were grown n 8-inch plastic pots and germinated plants were used for virus inovulaton t 10, 20 and 30 days after germinatin (dag).",
